    <descript>
      <abstract>The Rail Network is a comprehensive database of the nation's railway system including all railway mainlines, railroad yards, and major sidings in the continental U.S. at the 1:100,000 scale.  The data set covers the 48 contiguous States plus the District of Columbia.</abstract>
      <purpose>The data set provides location and partial attribute information for use in national and regional network analysis applications.</purpose>
    </descript>
